-- Name Bre Southstar
-- Race: dwarf
-- Sex: Female
-- Age: 16 human years (comment by Estralis: Doesn't really fit the description!)
-- Height: short
-- Weight: robust
-- Hair: long black
-- Eyes: red

-- Personality:
-- Amiable, very social, talkative, brave but scared, lazy.

-- Background:
-- Bre's parents when she was 10(human years) were killed by Cadomyrians on the road between Cadomyr and Galmair.
-- She was too young to even grasp the reason why. She made her way down a long road until she made it back to Galmair.
-- Back in Galmair she faced all the troubles a young girl has to face being homeless on the street. She passed from man to man,
-- who either died from sickness or sold her to another for a bit of drugs. It stopped being sad for her; it was merely a way of life.
-- Any hope of change died in her eyes. Over the next few years she was almost always owned by someone. In the off chance she wasn't
-- with someone she would beg on the street for food. During one of the times she saw a tall dwarf in grey armour stare at her. These
-- people disgusted her, the Civil Watch, the soldiers for the Don's army. They protect the rich people and always hurt the poor people.
-- That one tall soldier with shaved brown hair after staring at her for a few seconds left. The next day that soldier came back.
-- That soldier then asked. "Are you all right?" Surprisingly that tall dwarf was a girl. Bre meekly said yes. The tall dwarf walked away.

-- The next day the tall dwarf came back. She had a seared lamb leg in hand she gave it to Bre and with a haughty voice said,
-- "The street is no place for a girl, come with me. Bre shook her head. The tall dwarf walked away. Every day the tall dwarf came back asking
-- the same question. Bre would politely decline. It came to the point where Bre came to expect the tall dwarf, Gava and then came to wanting
-- her to come. One day when it was raining and cold Gava walked up and said, "It is cold and raining. This is no place for a young girl, come to my house.
-- "Bre answered "OK"

-- Gava walked Bre to her little wooden home. Bre felt really awkward. Gava boiled Bre some warm ale. Gava then just went to her bed and instantly fell asleep.
-- Bre sat by the warm fire. Tiredness overcame here and she passed out almost near as instant as Gava. Bre woke up to the aroma of fried goat strips and
-- boiled eagle eggs. Gava gave Bre the perfect older sister smile, they talked and from that day on they were sisters. An important day is the day when
-- Gava told Bre about the sister ritual she heard when she was little. And that was to use a dagger to make a prick on their left wrists, to tie them together
-- and swear sisterhood to each other.

-- A painful day was when Gava caught her using. Gava came home early to bring Bre some sweat bread. She caught Bre using some drugs. Gava started crying
-- and then Bre started crying. Bre ran out the house and slept on the street for four days. Gava came back and told her she can stay back at the house again.
-- Bre still uses and she knows it eats Gava up. It's a major source of her sadness. Bre and Gava worked to keep her using a secret.

-- Bre followed Gava into being an officer in the city watch and because of Gava's harsh training Bre despite being short and fat rose to the rank of Silverstone
-- and became a gate guard. A lot of the guys in the civil watch try to get with her, but she rejects them all.

-- Goals:
-- To be happy with her sister
-- To not be a burden to her sister

-- Methods:
-- To keep her using a secret
-- To work as a gate guard

-- (Civil Watch ranks)
-- The Don, Guilianni
-- Goldstone (lieutenant)
-- Silverstone (sergeants)
-- Copperstone (private)
-- Coalstone (recruit)

